<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-28T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1039.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-28T20:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your November 25, 3 p.m. You may inform Theodore that the Department is
                            ready to use its good offices with the Bank to secure, first, a small
                            loan to cover legitimate traveling expenses of the commission; second,
                            as soon as you report that the credentials of the commission are
                            satisfactory, a further loan to take care of the running expenses of the
                            Government during the time that the commission is in session.</p>
                        <p>Department’s November 24, 5 p.m., was drafted to prevent any possibility
                            of bad faith on the part of Théodore.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>